                           Many studies highlight the challenges facing incumbent firms in responding effectively to major technological transitions.
                              While some authors argue that these challenges can be overcome by firms possessing what have been called "dynamic capabilities,"
                              little work has described in detail the critical resources that these capabilities leverage, or the processes through which
                              these resources accumulate and evolve. This paper explores these issues through an in-depth exploratory case study of one
                              firm that has demonstrated consistently strong performance in an industry that is highly dynamic and uncertain


